Thank you @JacksonLeeTX18, @RepMikeQuigley, @RepDelBene , @RepCicilline, and @RepAdams for joining me for this week's @USProgressives hour!
We stand with women whose voices are seldom represented in legislative bodies filled with men ready to take away their rights. #StoptheSham
We stand with women who want to make their own choices about when, where & how to make decisions that will change their lives. #StoptheSham
Women should be able to have an abortion safely, without traveling hundreds of miles, or waiting weeks to be seen. #StoptheSham
.@USProgressives are here on the floor because we stand with women, in Texas and Louisiana and across the country. #StoptheSham
.@RepAdams:"A woman’s personal decisions should be between her & her doctor, NO ONE else! This obvious War on Women must stop!" #StoptheSham
.@RepCicilline: "I know that this is an extremely personal decision for women." #StoptheSham
.@RepDelBene: "Women deserve better. They deserve the freedom to make their own healthcare choices." #StoptheSham
.@RepMikeQuigley: "The decision in @WholeWomans Health will hold national implications. As a man, I am proud to stand up for choice."
@JacksonLeeTX18: "Human rights are women's rights." #StoptheSham
Women deserve to make the choices that work for them. These laws are an absolute farce, and it’s time to #StopTheSham
TX Policy Evaluation Project found that women who’ve reported barriers to abortion are more likely to self-induce an abortion. #StopTheSham
Laws like H.B. 2 are forcing more women down the dangerous path of attempting to end their pregnancies on their own. #StopTheSham
If H.B. 2 is allowed to go into effect, only 10 clinics will remain to serve the 5.4 million Texas women of reproductive age. #StopTheSham
In Texas, the full implementation of H.B. 2 would force more than 75 percent of abortion clinics to close. #StopTheSham
I find it hard to believe that organizations of physicians would oppose any of these laws if they really did make clinics safer #StopTheSham
They know what kinds of skills and resources are necessary for an abortion - one of the safest medical procedures out there. #StopTheSham
These laws are opposed by a host of leading medical groups, including the @AmerMedicalAssn and @acognews #StopTheSham
There is absolutely no logical, medical reason to suddenly require these clinics to meet the standards of hospitals.  #StopTheSham
Frankly, there’s no way the Texas law can be considered anything other than an undue burden. #StopTheSham
Women in Texas now have firsthand experience of what happens when states ignore the Supreme Court. #StopTheSham https://t.co/ygmCGBc2nl
The Court made it clear that states cannot use laws to create an undue burden for women seeking to exercise that right. #StopTheSham
SCOTUS decided, and set a precedent, that every woman in this nation has the constitutional right to an abortion. #StopTheSham
Roe v. Wade required SCOTUS to consider whether or not women had the right to make decisions about their bodies. #StoptheSham
.@RepJodie is proud that Texas always takes the lead in trying to turn back time for women. #StoptheSham https://t.co/XabwjLN0HG
.@GovernorPerry's ideal world is to limit women's access to reproductive care. #StopTheSham https://t.co/Qe7PjdFGQj
The men who passed these laws claimed they would increase medical accountability and safety of facilities that provide abortion.
The ruling in Louisiana all but guarantees the closure of 3 of 4 abortion clinics in that state unless the SCOTUS intervenes there as well.
Last night, the Fifth Circuit Court of Appeals allowed a similar law to move forward in Louisiana. #StoptheSham
Whole Women’s Health v. Hellerstedt case challenges Texas’s outright offensive effort to strip women of their right to choose. #StoptheSham
